International Presidents
Listed below are the twenty-seven International Presidents since the sorority's institution of the office in 1913.143 
Boul&lt;U+00E9&gt;

The Boul&lt;U+00E9&gt; is the regulating institution of the sorority and currently meets every two years.144 Throughout the years, notable individuals such as civil rights activists (Martin Luther King, Jr. and Roy Wilkins) and political figures (former U.S. Presidents Bill Clinton and Jimmy Carter) were speakers at past Boul&lt;U+00E9&gt; conferences.
Regions
 After the establishment of 32 graduate and undergraduate chapters in 1924, Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority organized chapters according to their regions in the United States and abroad. The Boul&lt;U+00E9&gt; determines the boundaries of the regions.145 The ten regions are each led by a regional director, where she serves a member of the sorority's Board of Directors. In addition to serving on the sorority's Board of Directors, the regional director also follows guidelines, program targets set by the International President, as well as procedures.146 Almost two-thirds of the sorority's regional directors have been elected international presidents.147 A comprehensive list of regions is shown below:



